It took me a sleepy morning moment to understand why you're passing the index value here (not its node, type, etc.). Let's give it a clearer name. :)

And I think by moving the spanning type last, we can avoid a special case. If we can't determine which index to look at, fall back to aggregating all types.

```suggestion
    def infer_indexed_type(self, at_index=None):
        container_type = self.get_container_type()
        if container_type.is_pytuple_type:
            if isinstance(at_index, int):
                return self.get_subscripted_type(at_index)
            return self.get_common_item_type()
```
